<h2 class="section4h2">KANYA VIDYA DHAN</h2>
<p class="section4p">KANYA VIDYA DHAN YOJNA is a scheme launched by the Uttar Pradesh government to provide financial assistance to meritorious girl students who have passed the 12th board examination. The scheme aims to encourage and support the higher education of girls who belong to economically weaker sections of the society. The scheme covers girl students who have passed the 12th board examination from any recognized board in Uttar Pradesh, such as UP Board, CBSE, ICSE, UP Madarsa Board, and UP Sanskrit Board. The scheme provides a one-time scholarship of Rs 30,000 to each eligible girl student. The scholarship amount is directly transferred to the bank account of the beneficiary. The scheme was started by former Chief Minister Akhilesh Yadav in 2012-13 and was revived by the current Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath in 2020-21. The scheme has benefited lakhs of girl students in Uttar Pradesh and has helped them pursue their dreams of higher education.</p>
