<h2 class="section4h2">KANYA SUMANGLA YOJNA</h2>
<p class="section4p">Kanya Sumangala Yojana is a scheme launched by the Uttar Pradesh government to provide financial assistance and social security to the girl child. The scheme aims to end female feticide, establish an equal gender ratio, stop the malpractice of child marriage, and improve the health and education of girls. The scheme covers six stages of a girl's life, from birth to graduation, and provides a lump sum amount at each stage. The scheme is applicable for two girls from a single family whose annual income is less than Rs. 3 lakh.</p>

<p class="section4p">Some of the features and benefits of the scheme are:<br />

- The scheme provides a total of Rs. 15,000 for each girl child in six installments.<br />
- The scheme encourages the parents to enroll their daughters in school and complete their education.<br />
- The scheme helps in reducing the dropout rate and increasing the literacy rate of girls.<br />
- The scheme promotes the empowerment and self-reliance of girls.<br />
- The scheme creates a positive attitude towards the birth of a girl child in the society.<br />

To apply for the scheme, the applicants need to register themselves on the official website of the Department of Women and Child Development. They need to provide valid Aadhaar numbers, birth registration numbers, and Parivaar IDs for themselves and their daughters. They also need to submit the required documents and certificates as per the stage of the scheme.<br />

For more information about the scheme, you can visit the following websites:<br /><br /></p>
<p>(1) DEPARTMENT OF WOMEN & CHILD DEVELOPMENT. &emsp; <a href="https://mksy.up.gov.in/.">Visit Website</a></p>
<p>(2) Kanya Sumangala Yojana - myScheme. &emsp; <a href="https://www.myscheme.gov.in/schemes/ksy">Visit Website</a></p><br />

